mily:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">picture of limited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">smaller size stock </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">availability was confirmed in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> recent sample of councils, meaning that, for the vast majority of tenants affecte</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">d by under occupancy deductions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">, there is no </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">real prospect of a move to avoid th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">reduction in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">the near future.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">There has been a massive demand for Discretionary Housing Payments – 22,000 at end of May (4 times the rate experienced last year for most councils).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">44% </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">of applicants were awarded DH</span><span styl